                           java.lang.String resourceId,
                           java.lang.String resourceType,
                           java.lang.String cursor,
                           java.lang.Boolean fetchAncestors,
                           java.lang.String includedFields,
                           java.lang.Long pageSize,
                           java.lang.Boolean sortAscending,
                           java.lang.String sortBy)
        Returns information about resources that are associated with the given resource. Id and type of the resource for which associated resources are to be fetched are to be specified as query parameter in the URI. Resource type of the associated resources must be specified as query parameter.

        Synchronous method overload. Result of the invocation will be reported as a method return value.

        Parameters:
        associatedResourceType - Resource type valid for use as target in association API (required)
        resourceId - The resource for which associated resources are to be fetched (required)
        resourceType - Resource type valid for use as source in association API (required)
        cursor - Opaque cursor to be used for getting next page of records (supplied by current result page) (optional)
        fetchAncestors - Fetch complete list of associated resources considering containment and nesting (optional, default to false)
        includedFields - Comma separated list of fields that should be included in query result (optional)
        pageSize - Maximum number of results to return in this page (server may return fewer) (optional, default to 1000)
        sortAscending - (optional)
        sortBy - Field by which records are sorted (optional)
        Returns:
        com.vmware.nsx.model.AssociationListResult
        Throws:
        com.vmware.vapi.std.errors.InvalidRequest - Bad Request, Precondition Failed
        com.vmware.vapi.std.errors.Unauthorized - Forbidden
        com.vmware.vapi.std.errors.ServiceUnavailable - Service Unavailable
        com.vmware.vapi.std.errors.InternalServerError - Internal Server Error
        com.vmware.vapi.std.errors.NotFound - Not Found
